# Aztec Packages Monorepo Overview

This document provides an overview of the Aztec Packages monorepo structure and key development areas.

## Core Packages

### `yarn-project/`
The TypeScript/JavaScript implementation of the Aztec protocol, containing:
- `aztec.js/` - Main SDK for interacting with Aztec
- `aztec-node/` - Node implementation
- `pxe/` - Private eXecution Environment
- `accounts/` - Account management
- `cli/` - Command-line interface tools
- `end-to-end/` - Integration tests

### `noir-projects/`
Zero-knowledge circuit implementations in Noir:
- `aztec-nr/` - Core Aztec circuits
- `noir-protocol-circuits/` - Protocol-specific circuits
- `noir-contracts/` - Smart contract interfaces

### `barretenberg/`
Core cryptographic implementation:
- `cpp/` - C++ cryptographic primitives
- `ts/` - TypeScript bindings
- `sol/` - Solidity contracts

### `l1-contracts/`
Layer 1 smart contracts:
- `src/core/` - Core protocol contracts
- `src/periphery/` - Peripheral contracts
- `src/governance/` - Governance contracts

## Supporting Infrastructure

### `boxes/`
Project templates and development environments:
- `react/` - React.js template
- `vanilla/` - Vanilla JS template
- `contract-only/` - Smart contract template

### `scripts/`
Development and deployment utilities:
- Build scripts
- Deployment tools
- Development utilities

### `iac/`
Infrastructure as Code:
- `network/` - Network deployment
- Cloud infrastructure templates

### `spartan/`
Testing and deployment infrastructure:
- Chaos testing scenarios
- Network deployment templates
- Metrics and monitoring

### `docs/`
Project documentation:
- Protocol specifications
- Developer guides
- API references

